docs.lead_paragraph: Syrian government troops pushed an offensive Tuesday against militants in the country's north on the eve of parliament elections — a vote that is expected to rubber-stamp an assembly loyal to President Bashar Assad ahead of a new round of peace talks in Geneva resuming this week.

headline.main: Syria Pushes Offensive on Eve of Elections, Talks in Geneva
